===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|i}}, two interwoven threads {{zh-l|*幺}} and a distinguishing mark {{zh-l|*亠}} on top. The whole character should represent a rope, as seen in [[率]] and [[弦]]. However, this rope is different from [[己]] and [[乃]].

===Etymology===
{{unknown|zh}}. The oldest basic color term for "black" which was later replaced by {{och-l|黑}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

One of its derivations is {{och-l|袨|a kind of black formal wear}}.

